As an expert in matrix operations, I can tell you that finding the inverse of a product of matrices is straightforward.  We use the property that (AB)⁻¹ = B⁻¹A⁻¹.

In this case, we're given:

*  A⁻¹ =  \begin{pmatrix} 4 & 0 \\ 1 & -1 \end{pmatrix}
*  B⁻¹ = \begin{pmatrix} 2 & -1 \\ -1 & 3 \end{pmatrix}

Therefore:

(AB)⁻¹ = B⁻¹A⁻¹ = \begin{pmatrix} 2 & -1 \\ -1 & 3 \end{pmatrix} \begin{pmatrix} 4 & 0 \\ 1 & -1 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 7 & 1 \\ -1 & -3 \end{pmatrix} 


So, the inverse of AB is:

$\boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 7 & 1 \\ -1 & -3 \end{pmatrix}}$
